My boyfriend I had a great experience at this wonderful atmospheric restaurant! The falafel was the best we've ever had. Served hot and crispy with yummy hummus and warm pita bread! We both had the Koshari for an entree. Again served hot and a huge portion with great sauce to go with. The service was great and we will definitely be back!

What a beautiful experience. Firstly the decor is absolutely amazing inside. The food is very tasty and authentic. From the appetizers, entrees and Feteer Nutella dessert! Everything was so delicious. Being from Brooklyn it’s extremely hard to find any authentic Egyptian cuisine. This is a great place for large parties or a night out with your partner/friend. There’s music playing in the background with dimmed lighting setting the perfect mood. If you are a hookah smoker then this is a win/win. You can smoke and eat while listening to some Arabic tunes. I can’t forget the great service by Huda!! She was very attentive and efficient. The owner also came by to say hello and make sure all was well. He seemed like a very nice guy who cared about his business and customers. I will definitely be back soon with more friends  :)

I normally don’t leave bad reviews but I really hope this restaurant change because it has a lot of potential. Few weeks ago my friends and I went to finally get some Egyptian food. They have two teens working with lack of experience. After ordering half of the menu because we were super excited and hungry. Our food took at least 45 mins. We didn’t care cause we were so hungry. We decided to order family style so we can all share and try from each other. The first thing my husband tried was the chicken kababs and it was super cold. We kept trying everything else and everything was cold. We waited at least another 10 mins for someone to come to us. My husband had to go all the way downstairs for them to come to us (btw there was no one in the store, they weren’t busy). We stated our concern with the food and made it clear that we didn’t want our food to be heated in the microwave, we weren’t going to pay over $200 for microwaved food. They literally came back with our food after 5 mins and all the plates looked exactly the same and we asked one of the teens if they microwaved it and they said YES with a nice smile. At this point my husband was really upset and didn’t want to eat there anymore. We asked them to call a manager and told them we didn’t want to eat. The owner came upstairs with an attitude and didn’t know how to fit the situation. Coming from a restaurant owning family I know how bad reviews can affect a restaurant but this was really needed. Please improve

I must admit, the food is good BUT the service is horrible. We came on a Friday night and they only had one person on the first floor and another on the third. It took them 20 minutes just to take our order and this was after asking several times and even getting up to tell them that no one took our order. When we made the order I asked several times if they could bring out the drink ASAP since I was super thirsty and, after waiting 30 minutes the food comes but of course not the drink. We asked again, finally got it. Once the food came, we asked that they setup the hookah so we don’t have to wait forever and after we were done eating we asked for the hookah which took another 30 minutes to come! It was like we were begging for them to give us what we were going to pay for anyway. The waiter was nice and it wasn’t his fault but it was clear that the owner is stingy and doesn’t want to pay more people. Oh and the owner was there, sitting. Couldn’t even help. It was a very aggravating experience for sure.

We are definitely coming back with Friends and Family and would recommend this place to everyone. A Truly Epicurean Delight. We ordered for two and were served for three. The Beef Kofta Kabob served with a Pilaf and Tahini, also the Stuffed Cabbage, was so delicious. The Hummus.. Everything was truly homemade. I am pretty sure that this restaurant does Not use MSG in their food like most restaurants do, because we did not get thirsty after we left. Kudos to the Chef and our complements  to the Owner. Also, much appreciation to Sami who took the time to explain the food and to give us a brief History on Alexandria. The service was amazing.

Let me start off with their A rating. I understand that when most of these restaurants have an A rating it should mean they are good and have good food...wrong. We went here for lunch and it took them about 15 minutes to even take a drink order and when we began to order we were told that 85% of the menu was NOT available at that time...so we settled and went with what was available. I ordered this Egypt macaroni thing and when it came out (with our drinks, finally) I took a few bites and hit.....frozen noodles. Yummy. I told the waitress that the center was frozen and she took it back and brought me a “new” one. She told me watch out the plate is hot but she didn’t say watch out your noodles are frozen again.
